The TRIANGLE, eventually deformed, is defined from
the 3 lines which define its 3 edges.

ATTENTION: The 3 lines must be given with a consecutive order or not

           |\ 
           |  \ 
          L3    L2
           |      \ 
           ---L1---\
ATTENTION:
The number of sub-triangles will be equal to the square
of the constant edge number of edges of the 3 lines.

Example: T9; I; 9; L1; L2; L3; 
Define a triangulation of contour the edges of lines L1 L2 L3
which have all the same number of edges.
